<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-08-16T18:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-08-13T19:00:00-05:00" n="592" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d592">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Governor Sir <persName type="from">W.
                                    MacGregor</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Earl of
                                    Elgin</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right">[<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1906-08-16T23:59:59+00:00" notBefore="1906-08-14T00:00:00+00:00">undated</date>] (Received
                                August 16, 1906.)</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 10.]</seg></opener>
                        <p>Have received from my ministers a comprehensive reply to your telegram
                            and Mr. Root’s communication. I shall forward copy by earliest
                            opportunity. Next mail leaves here Wednesday next.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>